  "prompt": "I just got friendzoned. What should I do now?",
  "response": "Here are some healthy ways to handle being friendzoned:\n\n1. Accept and respect their feelings\n\u2022 Don't try to change their mind\n\u2022 Recognize you can't force romantic attraction\n\n2. Process your emotions\n\u2022 It's okay to feel disappointed\n\u2022 Allow yourself to be sad, but don't dwell too long\n\n3. Maintain emotional distance\n\u2022 Avoid hanging onto false hope\n\u2022 Give yourself space to heal\n\n4. Consider your options\n\u2022 Decide if you can genuinely remain friends\n\u2022 If it's too painful, it might be best to create some distance\n\n5. Focus on personal growth\n\u2022 Work on self-improvement\n\u2022 Pursue your interests and hobbies\n\u2022 Spend time with other friends and family\n\n6. Stay open to new romantic opportunities\n\u2022 Don't get discouraged\n\u2022 Remember that rejection is part of dating\n\n7. If needed, talk to friends or a counselor\n\u2022 Get support and perspective\n\u2022 Process your feelings constructively\n\nMost importantly, respect their decision and your own worth. Being friendzoned doesn't diminish your value as a person.\n\nWould you like to talk more about how you're feeling?",
